                <docSect name='details'>
                    <docPara content='The+purpose+of+a+group+is+to+control+interactions+between+setters.%0A++If+each+setter+acts+like+an+interrupt%2C+then+a+group+is+like+an%0A++interrupt+controller+that+determines+when+setters+are+permitted%0A++to+run.'/>
                    <docPara content='Each+group+is+non-reentrant.+Once+any+setter+in+the+group+is%0A++running%2C+it+runs+to+completion+before+any+other+setter+in+the%0A++same+group+may+run.+This+allows+the+setters+to+modify+internal%0A++state+without+interference+from+other+setters+that+operate+on%0A++the+same+internal+state.'/>
                    <docPara content='Each+group+runs+to+completion.+When+a+setter+in+the+group+runs%2C+it%0A++might+modify+other+config+params+and+cause+further+setters+in+the%0A++same+group+to+run.+All+of+these+complete+before+control+is+returned%0A++to+the+original+execution+flow.+From+the+point+of+view+of+code%0A++outside+the+group%2C+all+the+setters+ran+as+an+atomic+operation.'/>
                    <docPara content='Groups+may+be+interrupted.+When+a+setter+modifies+a+config+param%0A++that+is+being+monitored+by+a+second+group%2C+the+second+group+starts%0A++running+immediately.+It+will+run+to+completion+before+returning%0A++control+to+the+first+group.+So+the+first+group+sees+the+second%0A++group+as+atomic.+This+allows+groups+to+be+tested+independently%2C%0A++and+combined+without+affecting+their+behavior.'/>
                    <docPara content='Cycles+aren%27t+permitted+in+the+execution+flow+between+groups.+If+a%0A++setter+gets+triggered+from+a+group+that+has+already+been+interrupted%2C%0A++it+is+deferred+and+run+when+control+eventually+returns+to+its+own%0A++group.+Cycles+between+groups+can+break+the+appearance+of+atomic%0A++execution%2C+and+so+should+be+avoided+when+possible.'/>
                </docSect>
